cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a framework for designing a neural multiplexer that can decide upon the appropriate model to be called for inference based on input and resource budgets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this framework for offloading hard inputs to the cloud, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on designing a light-weight neural multiplexer suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
